On Mon, 22 Sep 2003, Smith, Ted (T.A.) wrote:

> I have found that the blue nitrle gloves work much better. They do not break down when getting into the real slimey stuff.
>

I recommend nitrile gloves as well, they protect against all powerful
solvents, which latex does NOT. Nitriles are a bit stiff though, so the
latex are useful for simple dirt and grease work, but NOT for ANY solvent
exposure.

